SUMMARY:Online Fiction Critique Group
DESCRIPTION:Evanston Writers Workshop\nWelcome to the Evanston Writers Workshop Online Critique Group. We're a group of professional and aspiring writers who help each other polish our writing through workshop style critique. Writers have the opportunity to receive and give direct\, constructive\, and actionable feedback from attentive readers and writers who understand the craft of writing.\n\nWe will critique 2-3 submissions (maximum 3\,000 words each) per meeting.\nYou do not need to be a member to attend or critique\, however you need to be a member in order to submit and have your own work critiqued.\nIf you have a submission\, please submit it via this link:\nhttps://form.jotform.com/251125391424147\nby midnight the Friday before critique meeting.\n\nWe will meet monthly on the fourth Tuesday of the month. Although we've been critiquing in-person since 2007\, these are our first online meetings. Please visit the EWW website (https://evanstonwritersworkshop.org/#calendar-and-submission-links) to view current submissions.\n\nFiction writers of all levels of all genres are welcome\, ages 18+.\n\nFor more information\, submission guidelines and requirements\, please visit the Evanston Writers Workshop message board here evanstonwritersworkshop.org. Or you can direct questions to raven.reynolds.author@gmail.com.\n\nFriendly reminder: please send your submissions by the Friday (midnight) before the meeting.\n\nEWW is a not-for-profit 501 (C) 3 organization founded in 2007.
